In Alamofire 5rc1, `DataResponse` and the other response types became doubly generic, to both the value serialized from the response and the error type produced. By default Alamofire&#39;s response handlers will always produce `AFError` error values, so there are now `AF*Response` `typealias`es that default to that error type.

Additionally, you shouldn&#39;t use `responseJSON` if you have `Codable` types, just use `responseDecodable`:

```swift
private static func request&lt;T: Codable&gt; (_ urlConvertible: URLRequestConvertible) -&gt; Observable&lt;T&gt; {
    return Observable&lt;T&gt;.create { observer in
        let request = AF.request(urlConvertible).responseDecodable(of: T.self) { response in ... }
    }
}

